column13: Our cars get extremely hot after sitting in the sun all day. Adding shades over the parking lot would help protect them. Could you please consider this?

Some drivers are using the lane in front of the parking entrance to drop off students, causing delays for those trying to park. This is especially frustrating because there are two designated drop-off lanes available. Also, after 12 PM, buses and vans are waiting in the parking lot for students, often blocking available parking spots closer to the gate. 
 I suggest either returning to the previous system, where a different entrance was used for parking only, or enforcing a no-drop-off rule in the lane where the parking entrance is located.
